typeDescriptions.typeString: function (contract ERC20WithTokenInfo,enum ISuperTokenFactory.Upgradability,string memory,string memory) external returns (contract ISuperToken)

deployNativeAssetSuperToken(string,strin.details: e.g. ETHx, MATICx, AVAXx, etc. The underlying is the Native Asset.

deployPureSuperToken(string,string,uint2.details: We specify the initial supply (because non-downgradeable) on creation and send it to the deployer

params._initialSupply: The initial token supply of the pure super token

deployWrapperSuperToken(string,string,ui.details: SuperToken name and symbol format: `Super ${_underlyingSymbol}` and `${_underlyingSymbol}x`, respectively

transferOwnership(address).details: This function allows you to transfer ownership of TestGovernance when testing

params.newOwner: the new owner of the TestGovernance contract

deployNativeAssetSuperToken(string,strin.notice: Deploys a Native Asset Super Token and lists it in the resolver

deployPureSuperToken(string,string,uint2.notice: Deploys a Pure Super Token and lists it in the resolver

deployWrapperSuperToken(string,string,ui.notice: Deploys an ERC20 and a Wrapper Super Token for the ERC20 and lists both in the resolver

transferOwnership(address).notice: Transfer ownership of the TestGovernance contract
